1
00:01:15,789 --> 00:01:17,524
–Mom?
–I am here.

2
00:01:27,149 --> 00:01:28,241
Mom!

3
00:01:34,189 --> 00:01:35,695
You forgot that.

4
00:01:36,973 --> 00:01:39,013
Are you sure
this is the right thing?

5
00:01:39,053 --> 00:01:42,007
It feels like it'd be better
if we thought about it.

6
00:01:43,373 --> 00:01:47,607
–Yeah, I do.
–We don't have any other option.

7
00:01:50,093 --> 00:01:51,119
Okay.

8
00:02:00,589 --> 00:02:02,837
If I get off early
I can pick you up.

9
00:02:02,893 --> 00:02:04,963
It don't matter,
I will take a bus.

10
00:02:06,349 --> 00:02:07,538
Don't worry.

11
00:02:08,589 --> 00:02:11,089
–Have a good day.
–You too, Mom.

12
00:02:27,821 --> 00:02:30,735
–How you doing?
–I don't know.

13
00:02:32,877 --> 00:02:34,994
How we're paying
for all of this?

14
00:02:36,365 --> 00:02:39,376
–We put up the house.
–I knew it.

15
00:02:41,389 --> 00:02:43,768
It's because of you
I am still alive.

16
00:02:45,421 --> 00:02:47,221
We decided it together.

17
00:02:47,629 --> 00:02:50,193
What did you all
decide together?

18
00:02:51,469 --> 00:02:53,073
To live on the street?

19
00:02:54,285 --> 00:02:56,184
For 18 years…

20
00:02:56,781 --> 00:02:59,957
your mother and I have been
paying on that house…

21
00:03:01,421 --> 00:03:03,254
just to fuck it all up.

22
00:03:03,981 --> 00:03:05,880
Don't say that, Dad.

23
00:04:21,613 --> 00:04:22,901
I am leaving, babe.

24
00:04:22,957 --> 00:04:25,189
You got what
you have been waiting for?

25
00:04:25,229 --> 00:04:26,229
Yeah, I got it.

26
00:04:26,797 --> 00:04:28,051
Would it be right?

27
00:04:28,493 --> 00:04:30,228
That's not your concern.

28
00:04:30,637 --> 00:04:34,293
But if I make it back,
I going to make so much money…

29
00:04:35,053 --> 00:04:36,821
you going to love me again.

30
00:05:11,053 --> 00:05:14,894
When I turned five years old,
I got a little kitten.

31
00:05:14,957 --> 00:05:17,829
It was so cute I took
it to bed with me every night.

32
00:05:17,869 --> 00:05:19,161
I want a little lamb…

33
00:05:19,181 --> 00:05:21,573
and I will take it to bed
with me at night.

34
00:05:21,613 --> 00:05:23,893
People don't keep sheep inside.

35
00:05:23,949 --> 00:05:25,869
–I will.
–Didn't you hear?

36
00:05:25,933 --> 00:05:29,029
We don't keep sheep inside
and we don't take them to bed.

37
00:05:29,069 --> 00:05:32,496
My little lamb has to be
all white with black ears.

38
00:05:32,557 --> 00:05:33,976
Why black ears?

39
00:05:34,029 --> 00:05:36,741
So I won't get him mixed up
with the other sheep.

40
00:05:36,781 --> 00:05:39,280
I will be able to recognize him.

41
00:05:39,341 --> 00:05:40,400
Very clever.

42
00:05:41,677 --> 00:05:43,117
Thanks, Mom.

43
00:06:09,645 --> 00:06:11,445
Two million dollars, Jasper.

44
00:06:11,501 --> 00:06:13,367
I get back $3 million in 3 days.

45
00:06:15,405 --> 00:06:17,304
You said $2.5.

46
00:06:25,549 --> 00:06:28,495
–I'll take it.
–You can count it.

47
00:06:46,061 --> 00:06:49,553
I'm sorry to say, but
he'll need another operation.

48
00:06:50,189 --> 00:06:52,502
Unfortunately
we can't always foresee…

49
00:06:52,558 --> 00:06:54,565
consequences
in this type of cases.

50
00:06:54,605 --> 00:06:57,071
How much is this operation
gonna cost?

51
00:06:57,133 --> 00:07:00,035
I assume it would be so much
as the past procedure.

52
00:07:03,085 --> 00:07:04,209
All right.

53
00:07:05,581 --> 00:07:06,665
Thank you Doctor.

54
00:07:29,709 --> 00:07:32,087
So what's thisjob about, man?
Dope?

55
00:07:32,141 --> 00:07:33,811
No. Nothing like that.

56
00:07:33,869 --> 00:07:36,597
Listen, I am broke.
I am on the street.

57
00:07:37,997 --> 00:07:38,997
Hey.

58
00:07:39,725 --> 00:07:42,887
I haven't forgotten what you did
for me when I was away.

59
00:07:44,301 --> 00:07:47,858
If this thing works out.
I will set you up. I promise.

60
00:07:47,917 --> 00:07:51,507
–How long exactly will it take?
–One day.

61
00:07:52,237 --> 00:07:55,379
Jesus. You make
all that cash in one day?

62
00:07:55,437 --> 00:07:56,496
If I make it.

63
00:07:57,741 --> 00:07:59,501
But you made it the last time.

64
00:08:00,461 --> 00:08:02,196
That was last time.

65
00:08:04,141 --> 00:08:07,414
As long as my luck doesn't
run out, you can count on me.

66
00:09:33,261 --> 00:09:36,622
Do you still live at 135,
Kissam Avenue, Talbot Ohio?

67
00:09:37,101 --> 00:09:38,127
Yeah.

68
00:09:45,997 --> 00:09:49,107
Okay Vincent, I think
that about does it. Thank you.

69
00:11:07,469 --> 00:11:10,797
I'm here to pick up a package
for William Harrison.

70
00:11:11,533 --> 00:11:13,999
–ID please.
–Sure.

71
00:11:55,533 --> 00:11:57,814
There is a train ticket
for New York…

72
00:11:58,189 --> 00:12:01,911
and the CPS receipt
for pick-up.

73
00:12:02,829 --> 00:12:04,421
We know
about the envelope…

74
00:12:04,461 --> 00:12:06,373
we opened it
before your husband.

75
00:12:06,413 --> 00:12:07,413
And?

76
00:12:08,333 --> 00:12:11,443
There was no CPS receipt
in the envelope.

77
00:12:11,501 --> 00:12:15,309
That's your problem.
I got enough for my own.

78
00:12:17,453 --> 00:12:18,479
Okay.

79
00:12:19,789 --> 00:12:21,207
Thank you.

80
00:12:22,349 --> 00:12:23,349
Thank you.

81
00:12:26,029 --> 00:12:30,197
Here it is. Harrison.
Picked up by Al Vincent Farrow.

82
00:12:38,445 --> 00:12:39,700
Yeah, it's him.

83
00:12:48,045 --> 00:12:50,806
What do you think?
How do I look?

84
00:12:51,405 --> 00:12:53,304
You're very handsome.

85
00:12:54,317 --> 00:12:55,790
They're gonna love you.

86
00:14:09,741 --> 00:14:12,436
<i>–Hello?
–Mr Harrison?</i>

87
00:14:12,493 --> 00:14:13,493
Yeah.

88
00:14:15,181 --> 00:14:16,403
<i>Tomorrow at noon…</i>

89
00:14:16,461 --> 00:14:18,757
<i>go to the PostNet store
by Grand Central.</i>

90
00:14:18,797 --> 00:14:22,071
<i>–Hang on.
–200 West, 39th Street.</i>

91
00:14:23,245 --> 00:14:24,272
Okay.

92
00:14:24,589 --> 00:14:27,415
<i>With the key you found
with the cell phone…</i>

93
00:14:27,469 --> 00:14:28,909
<i>you'll open box 253.</i>

94
00:14:29,293 --> 00:14:32,785
<i>Inside you'll find another train
ticket and more instructions.</i>

95
00:14:35,278 --> 00:14:40,046
<i>The ticket is for Macomb, but
you'll get off one stop before.</i>

96
00:14:40,109 --> 00:14:42,128
<i>One stop before.</i>

97
00:15:30,029 --> 00:15:31,502
Ticket, please.

98
00:15:46,477 --> 00:15:48,309
He's getting off at Macomb.

99
00:15:49,613 --> 00:15:53,105
–What time do we arrive?
–Train gets in at 3:10.

100
00:15:54,573 --> 00:15:56,591
Can I help you
with anything else?

101
00:15:56,973 --> 00:15:58,479
No. Thank you.

102
00:16:21,133 --> 00:16:22,965
–You free?
–Yeah, get in.

103
00:16:43,853 --> 00:16:45,807
That'll be $77.

104
00:16:46,829 --> 00:16:49,557
–Keep the change.
–Wow! Thank you.

105
00:17:47,821 --> 00:17:49,294
Give me your phone.

106
00:17:55,309 --> 00:17:56,401
Get in the car.

107
00:18:38,925 --> 00:18:43,311
I brought him down here
and that's it. And I left.

108
00:18:46,061 --> 00:18:48,133
You didn't see
anything else unusual?

109
00:18:48,173 --> 00:18:49,173
No.

110
00:19:06,765 --> 00:19:09,558
–Which number is he?
–Thirteen.

111
00:19:21,581 --> 00:19:23,567
Stay in the middle
of the carpet.

112
00:19:27,341 --> 00:19:29,011
Take your clothes off.

113
00:19:41,325 --> 00:19:42,678
Take off the rest.

114
00:19:52,301 --> 00:19:53,774
Get dressed.

115
00:20:28,781 --> 00:20:30,254
Follow me.

116
00:20:37,837 --> 00:20:39,026
Have a seat.

117
00:21:10,893 --> 00:21:12,432
Who's that?

118
00:21:13,357 --> 00:21:14,710
I can explain.

119
00:21:15,341 --> 00:21:16,847
–I know…
–Shut up!

120
00:21:18,829 --> 00:21:20,150
Go get Jack.

121
00:21:28,717 --> 00:21:30,269
You're probably wondering…

122
00:21:30,733 --> 00:21:32,632
what I'm doing here.
–Quiet!

123
00:22:02,893 --> 00:22:04,311
Two million.

124
00:22:04,749 --> 00:22:08,023
I'll bet $700·000 on number six.

125
00:22:09,037 --> 00:22:10,096
What's going on?

126
00:22:11,149 --> 00:22:12,403
Who is he?

127
00:22:12,461 --> 00:22:15,091
The guy I picked up
at the intersection.

128
00:22:15,149 --> 00:22:17,048
He's not who I was expecting.

129
00:22:17,645 --> 00:22:20,558
–Well, he had the number.
–Harrison's dead.

130
00:22:21,869 --> 00:22:24,401
–What are you talking about?
–He OD'd.

131
00:22:24,845 --> 00:22:27,191
And who the fuck are you?

132
00:22:29,069 --> 00:22:32,495
I'm an electrician.
I was working on his house.

133
00:22:35,853 --> 00:22:38,917
–Did he tell you about this?
–No, I overheard him talking.

134
00:22:38,957 --> 00:22:42,417
He was waiting for a letter
and it could be a lot of money.

135
00:22:42,477 --> 00:22:44,807
I took it
and followed the instructions.

136
00:22:45,805 --> 00:22:48,402
–Do you know what this is about?
–No.

137
00:22:49,005 --> 00:22:50,576
No, I have no idea.

138
00:22:56,013 --> 00:22:57,202
Follow me.

139
00:23:01,805 --> 00:23:03,637
Do you think the cops sent him?

140
00:23:06,445 --> 00:23:09,075
Maybe we should get out now.

141
00:23:09,645 --> 00:23:11,794
If we leave
and the cops show up…

142
00:23:11,853 --> 00:23:14,286
the others will think
we ratted.

143
00:23:14,669 --> 00:23:16,142
We'd be dead men.

144
00:23:19,565 --> 00:23:22,293
–Where you going?
–I should go talk to them.

145
00:23:26,061 --> 00:23:28,526
Excuse me, gentlemen.

146
00:23:29,581 --> 00:23:31,414
If it's a problem…

147
00:23:32,045 --> 00:23:33,911
me being here, then…

148
00:23:33,965 --> 00:23:36,660
then I think I should leave.
I'll leave.

149
00:23:36,718 --> 00:23:38,355
It's too late.

150
00:23:42,445 --> 00:23:45,326
–Where are they?
–They're in there.

151
00:23:48,749 --> 00:23:50,254
Is your man here?

152
00:23:50,317 --> 00:23:52,881
Yes, he's here.
Everything's okay.

153
00:23:52,941 --> 00:23:54,610
We start in a half hour.

154
00:23:54,989 --> 00:23:56,757
We'll be right down.

155
00:24:00,781 --> 00:24:04,589
–What if I don't want me here?
–You have to play now.

156
00:24:05,421 --> 00:24:07,854
I don't know
what that means, but…

157
00:24:08,493 --> 00:24:10,032
You'll find out.

158
00:24:12,877 --> 00:24:16,205
Six hundred thousand
on number thirteen.

159
00:24:21,933 --> 00:24:23,352
Good luck.

160
00:25:04,813 --> 00:25:07,923
Attention! The first round
is about to begin!

161
00:25:08,653 --> 00:25:09,744
You can have it.

162
00:25:09,805 --> 00:25:13,427
I'm asking the guards to
please distribute the bullets.

163
00:25:13,485 --> 00:25:16,366
One bullet to each player.

164
00:25:21,773 --> 00:25:22,962
Hans…

165
00:25:23,661 --> 00:25:29,008
we are born only once
and we die only once.

166
00:25:29,613 --> 00:25:32,756
You must be philosophical, huh?

167
00:25:32,813 --> 00:25:37,135
You are the descendant
of the great Schopenhauer.

168
00:26:05,069 --> 00:26:07,928
I ask all the gamblers
To back up a little.

169
00:26:09,613 --> 00:26:13,039
Please, gentlemen, back up.
Back up.

170
00:26:15,949 --> 00:26:17,520
Thank you gentlemen.

171
00:26:24,173 --> 00:26:27,032
Please, boss, have a seat.

172
00:26:28,813 --> 00:26:30,253
Players!

173
00:26:31,373 --> 00:26:35,924
Load your bullets
into their cylinders!

174
00:26:46,189 --> 00:26:48,056
What going on, thirteen?

175
00:26:48,109 --> 00:26:51,023
Do you have a problem,
number thirteen?

176
00:26:54,029 --> 00:26:54,981
Watch out.

177
00:26:55,021 --> 00:26:57,400
No, no one get up into the ring!

178
00:26:57,453 --> 00:26:59,537
I ask you to step down
immediately!

179
00:26:59,597 --> 00:27:02,510
He doesn't know how
to load his gun. Give it here.

180
00:27:04,269 --> 00:27:06,485
Pay attention.
Open it like this.

181
00:27:07,149 --> 00:27:08,149
Round.

182
00:27:13,165 --> 00:27:15,381
All right! Enough!

183
00:27:20,589 --> 00:27:22,095
Take your places!

184
00:27:25,645 --> 00:27:27,959
Raise your weapons!

185
00:27:33,069 --> 00:27:34,324
Higher!

186
00:27:37,325 --> 00:27:39,191
Spin your cylinders!

187
00:27:42,029 --> 00:27:43,764
More, more, keep it up!

188
00:27:50,701 --> 00:27:51,858
Stop!

189
00:27:54,221 --> 00:27:55,542
Aim!

190
00:28:00,301 --> 00:28:02,101
Cock your hammers!

191
00:28:06,669 --> 00:28:10,030
Number thirteen,
no turning around!

192
00:28:13,997 --> 00:28:17,718
Players, all eyes on the bulb!

193
00:28:17,773 --> 00:28:21,559
When the bulb lights up,
you shoot!

194
00:29:11,501 --> 00:29:14,415
Number thirteen did not shoot!

195
00:29:14,925 --> 00:29:18,646
Mr Joe Gerber, if your man
does not shoot, we will!

196
00:29:22,925 --> 00:29:26,252
What the fuck are you doing?
Pull the trigger!

197
00:29:27,309 --> 00:29:32,056
–Shoot! Shoot, son of a bitch!
–I'm going to count to three!

198
00:29:32,109 --> 00:29:34,292
–Shoot!
–Shoot!

199
00:29:34,349 --> 00:29:35,407
Two!

200
00:29:45,133 --> 00:29:48,592
Everyone out of the ring!

201
00:29:53,773 --> 00:29:56,086
Are you done
with your little drama?

202
00:30:02,765 --> 00:30:05,624
How much are they paying you
to watch my ass?

203
00:30:06,541 --> 00:30:08,145
What the fuck is it to you?

204
00:30:08,173 --> 00:30:11,566
I'll give you fifty times more
what they're giving you…

205
00:30:11,629 --> 00:30:13,681
if you let me
get out of here.

206
00:30:13,741 --> 00:30:16,622
If you got that money,
why did you come here?

207
00:30:19,021 --> 00:30:21,934
Do you think I waltzed
through the fucking door?

208
00:30:47,213 --> 00:30:50,453
–What's going on, man?
–Get dressed, fucker!

209
00:30:58,637 --> 00:31:01,496
<i>Gringo, gringo.
Where are you going, gringo?</i>

210
00:31:13,997 --> 00:31:17,008
Hi, boss. Very nice to see you.

211
00:31:17,677 --> 00:31:20,055
It must be really important…

212
00:31:20,717 --> 00:31:22,932
ifyou want to talk
this late.

213
00:31:24,557 --> 00:31:25,811
Put him in the box.

214
00:31:26,158 --> 00:31:29,649
Wait. What are you doing?
What the fuck are you doing?

215
00:31:32,941 --> 00:31:38,222
Damn it! Get me the fuck
outta here! God damn!

216
00:31:53,549 --> 00:31:55,502
Unshackle his legs.

217
00:31:58,189 --> 00:31:59,585
Are you in charge here?

218
00:31:59,629 --> 00:32:01,647
You gonna tell me
what's going on?

219
00:32:02,189 --> 00:32:05,648
I've been in this goddamn box
for two and a half days!

220
00:32:05,709 --> 00:32:07,793
What's going on.
What do you want?

221
00:32:07,853 --> 00:32:11,410
Give him a shower, a change
of clothes. Something fresh.

222
00:32:11,469 --> 00:32:12,528
What are you…?

223
00:32:12,589 --> 00:32:15,187
–And his stuff?
–What are you talking about?

224
00:32:16,269 --> 00:32:17,906
Give it to him.

225
00:32:20,205 --> 00:32:23,730
I can't do nothing foryou,
don't even think about it.

226
00:32:23,789 --> 00:32:26,135
–It's not possible.
–Wait a minute.

227
00:32:26,189 --> 00:32:28,786
Come on, come here.
Come here, man.

228
00:32:40,365 --> 00:32:43,409
My man is out.
I wanna bet on yours.

229
00:32:43,469 --> 00:32:46,677
Sure. I take
50 points off the top.

230
00:32:51,085 --> 00:32:53,617
–You want some morphine?
–No.

231
00:32:54,765 --> 00:32:56,849
–They all do it.
–I said no!

232
00:33:05,229 --> 00:33:07,346
You lost your player,
didn't you?

233
00:33:07,405 --> 00:33:08,405
Son of a bitch.

234
00:33:08,461 --> 00:33:10,742
Sure you're betting
on the right man?

235
00:33:10,798 --> 00:33:13,591
Don't worry about him,
he has what he needs.

236
00:33:14,669 --> 00:33:17,381
I don't know what you deal
with this guy is, but…

237
00:33:17,421 --> 00:33:19,505
I can do you one better.
60/40.

238
00:33:19,565 --> 00:33:21,846
Sixty for you,
forty for me.

239
00:33:21,901 --> 00:33:24,596
But you have to bet
at least $400·000.

240
00:33:24,653 --> 00:33:27,348
The player number six
has the most experience.

241
00:33:27,405 --> 00:33:30,411
–You know who I'm talking about?
–I know your player.

242
00:33:30,445 --> 00:33:33,272
You made your offer,
I just made mine.

243
00:33:33,325 --> 00:33:35,704
Let this gentleman
make up his own mind.

244
00:33:37,901 --> 00:33:39,701
Sixty-forty it is.

245
00:33:42,605 --> 00:33:44,373
Place your bets, gentlemen.

246
00:34:16,141 --> 00:34:19,829
Your brother would fare better
if family visited more often.

247
00:34:19,885 --> 00:34:22,744
A year's a long time
for someone in his condition.

248
00:34:22,798 --> 00:34:25,143
I'm the only family
Ronald Lynn has.

249
00:34:25,965 --> 00:34:28,464
I try to get down here
as often as I can.

250
00:34:28,525 --> 00:34:31,351
To skip his medication,
even for a day…

251
00:34:31,405 --> 00:34:34,199
could be serious.
–Yes, ma'am.

252
00:34:37,997 --> 00:34:41,390
Sign here and here
for Ronald Lynn's release.

253
00:34:50,797 --> 00:34:54,354
Your brother's here. He came
to get you. You have to go.

254
00:35:08,685 --> 00:35:10,868
–Did they take care of you?
–Yeah.

255
00:35:12,525 --> 00:35:14,609
–Good.
