if they were looking
for Harrison?

526
01:09:50,989 --> 01:09:53,553
The driver didn't know Harrison.

527
01:09:53,613 --> 01:09:56,592
When he pulled up,
I flashed him the signal.

528
01:09:56,653 --> 01:09:58,159
The signal?

529
01:09:58,893 --> 01:10:01,425
A piece of corkboard
with a number.

530
01:10:12,461 --> 01:10:16,083
–Where did he drop you?
–Somewhere in the forest.

531
01:10:16,845 --> 01:10:18,350
What happened?

532
01:10:19,565 --> 01:10:22,478
When I got there, two guys
were waiting in a car.

533
01:10:24,525 --> 01:10:26,990
When they saw me,
I knew I was screwed.

534
01:10:27,565 --> 01:10:29,681
I told them
Harrison was dead…

535
01:10:29,741 --> 01:10:32,054
that I was willing
to take his place.

536
01:10:32,109 --> 01:10:33,909
But they didn't go for it.

537
01:10:34,349 --> 01:10:36,848
Either they didn't believe me
or whatever…

538
01:10:36,909 --> 01:10:38,719
but they
didn't want me there.

539
01:10:39,341 --> 01:10:41,261
I saw one of them had a gun.

540
01:10:41,325 --> 01:10:43,922
When he reached for it,
I reacted.

541
01:10:44,525 --> 01:10:48,016
–I ran and just kept running.
–Did they chase you?

542
01:10:48,077 --> 01:10:50,226
They chased me.
They shot at me.

543
01:10:52,781 --> 01:10:54,647
But I just kept running.

544
01:10:55,661 --> 01:10:58,356
I ran so hard I lost
the heels of my shoes.

545
01:11:07,981 --> 01:11:11,247
If you saw them again, would you
be able to identify them?

546
01:11:11,821 --> 01:11:12,912
Of course.

547
01:11:14,605 --> 01:11:17,300
Could you take me
to that place in the forest?

548
01:11:17,773 --> 01:11:19,475
I was in a panic.

549
01:11:19,533 --> 01:11:22,709
I'd been running for hours,
it was dark.

550
01:11:22,765 --> 01:11:25,669
How the fuck do you expect me
to remember where I was?

551
01:11:25,709 --> 01:11:27,909
But if we took you
to that intersection…

552
01:11:27,949 --> 01:11:29,811
you'd get
your bearings, right?

553
01:11:32,365 --> 01:11:34,515
The driver blindfolded me.

554
01:11:36,973 --> 01:11:40,432
–You're lying.
–I'm telling the truth.

555
01:11:45,325 --> 01:11:47,158
Put your boots back on.

556
01:12:06,157 --> 01:12:07,543
Can I go now?

557
01:14:11,853 --> 01:14:13,937
Twenty-two dollars, please.

558
01:14:30,445 --> 01:14:32,725
<i>–Mom?
–Vince.</i>

559
01:14:32,781 --> 01:14:35,575
<i>How's Dad? How's everything?</i>

560
01:14:35,629 --> 01:14:38,772
<i>Everything's the same.
He was wondering about you.</i>

561
01:14:38,829 --> 01:14:41,055
What happened?
Did everything go okay?

562
01:14:41,389 --> 01:14:43,875
Listen, Mom, I sent
some money on the mail.

563
01:14:44,173 --> 01:14:45,875
Certified mail.

564
01:14:45,933 --> 01:14:47,887
<i>–Money?
–A lot of money.</i>

565
01:14:47,949 --> 01:14:51,506
If you're not home,
have Clara wait for it, okay?

566
01:14:51,565 --> 01:14:53,943
<i>What do you mean, money?
From where?</i>

567
01:14:53,997 --> 01:14:57,303
I'll explain later, just
make sure somebody's home.

568
01:14:57,358 --> 01:15:00,751
You're scaring me, Vincent.
Are you in trouble?

569
01:15:00,813 --> 01:15:02,417
<i>No, everything's fine.</i>

570
01:15:02,477 --> 01:15:05,456
Just make sure somebody's
home tomorrow, okay?

571
01:15:05,517 --> 01:15:07,863
<i>Vincent, please tell me
what's going on.</i>

572
01:15:07,918 --> 01:15:08,976
I love you.

573
01:16:09,901 --> 01:16:11,287
$18.25.

574
01:16:15,053 --> 01:16:16,658
How much for the lamb?

575
01:16:17,837 --> 01:16:21,394
–It's not for sale.
–I'll give you $100 for it.

576
01:16:21,773 --> 01:16:23,792
–For the lamb?
–Yeah.

577
01:18:23,821 --> 01:18:24,912
It's snowing.

578
01:18:29,197 --> 01:18:30,289
Yeah.

579
01:18:36,557 --> 01:18:37,877
Going far?

580
01:18:39,949 --> 01:18:41,520
I'm going home.

581
01:18:43,533 --> 01:18:44,690
Where?

582
01:18:48,077 --> 01:18:49,233
Ohio.

583
01:19:52,685 --> 01:19:54,583
<i>We put up the house.</i>

584
01:19:55,565 --> 01:19:57,791
<i>It'd be better
if we thought about it.</i>

585
01:19:59,693 --> 01:20:02,705
<i>I'm here to pick up a package
for William Harrison.</i>

586
01:20:05,773 --> 01:20:09,100
<i>I'm sorry to say, but
he'll need another operation.</i>

587
01:20:12,013 --> 01:20:14,083
<i>With all that cash,
you'll love me.</i>

588
01:20:15,885 --> 01:20:19,606
<i>My little lamb has to be
all white with black ears.</i>

589
01:20:22,253 --> 01:20:23,988
<i>You're very handsome.</i>

590
01:20:25,229 --> 01:20:26,702
<i>They're gonna love you.</i>

